org.intellimate.izou.security

Class PermissionModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.intellimate.izou.util.IzouModule
      • org.intellimate.izou.security.PermissionModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Identifiable, MainProvider
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AudioPermissionModule, FilePermissionModule, ReflectionPermissionModule, RootPermission, SocketPermissionModule

    public abstract class PermissionModule
extends IzouModule
    A PermissionModule defines basic permissions in Izou. A permission in Izou is defined as service that is generally allowed, yet the addOn has to be registered in order to use the service.

    For example, socket connections are generally allowed for Izou addOns yet in order to use them their usage has to be declared in the addon_config.properties file of the addOn.

    Thus PermissionModule implements a registration system for services like socket connection.
